<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Description.</emphasis>
Body granulate, small size, slender and macropronotal (
<figureCitation box="[931,1065,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Figs. 6A, B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1086,1159,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Head:</emphasis>
frontal costa bifurcation located near to the top of vertex; scutellum narrow, with carinae almost parallel; lower margin of the antennal grooves located between of the lower margin of the compound eyes (
<figureCitation box="[961,1053,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Eyes subglobose, with rounded dorsal surface and straight ventral margin (in lateral view) and elevated higher than vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1275,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); lateral ocelli placed on the side of the costa frontal, medial ocellus located on the lower margin of the scutellum and as wide as lateral ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[304,391,871,898]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Antennae elongated and filiform, more than 2.5 times longer than the fore-femur, with 13-14 segments; vertex little wider than one of the eyes in dorsal and frontal views, truncate anteriorly; median carinae present and short. Facial outline sub-vertical, rounded between the connection of the facial carinae and the frontal carinae. Fastigium of the vertex not produced in lateral view; fastigio-fascial angle rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1277,979,1006]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); frontal costa mid-length and connected with the facial carinae and reaching near the middle of the face; palpi whitish, with first three segments cylindrical and last two rounded and flattened (
<figureCitation box="[879,971,1051,1078]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[993,1124,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Pronotum:</emphasis>
Slender, surpassing the tip of hind femora and abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[499,590,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Pronotal disc almost flat, with an undulation at the level of the prozone, widened between the humeral angles; anteriorly straight, posterior apex pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1183,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles and lateral shoulder carinae rounded; lateral lobe subrounded below, notoriously prolongated latero-ventrally; infrascapular area very slim and short; lateral area moderately widened (
<figureCitation box="[906,996,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Post humeral spot present or not (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[197,213,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[188,1398,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. Color variation A. Color form 2. B. Form 3. C. Form 4. D. Form 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785352/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">7</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,317,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Wings.</emphasis>
Tegmina ovoid, wings well developed reaching to apex of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1189,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1209,1272,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore and midfemora compressed, carinated with undulations, most conspicuous on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1124,1278,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6D, E, F</figureCitation>
); hind femora with ante-genicular tooth little developed; hind tibia ampliated from the base to the apex; the first article of the tarsi of the hind leg, subequal to the second and third articles united. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[871,1087,1339,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Terminalia: Male.</emphasis>
Penultimate male sternite with posterior margin straight (
<figureCitation box="[448,540,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate slender, triangular-shaped in ventral view and divided at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[220,311,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
); cerci small and conical (
<figureCitation box="[608,699,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[719,814,1411,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Female.</emphasis>
Ovipositor normal, with the apex of dorsal and ventral valves sharped (
<figureCitation box="[332,486,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Figs. 6I and J</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate emarginated along ventro-apical edge (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1208,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
